                <p><name type="person" key="384"><hi rend="initialcap">A</hi>RTUS, <hi
                            rend="initialcap">C</hi>HARLES</name>, Private, <name
                        type="organization" key="370">Co. I, 15th New York Artillery</name>, aged 30
                    years.  Contusion of the left temporal by a piece of shell.  <name type="battle" key="90">Weldon Railroad</name>,
                        <date type="injury" when="1864-08-20">August 20th, 1864</date>.  Treated at
                    field hospital of Fifth Corps, and <name type="hospital" key="165">Mount
                        Pleasant</name>, Washington.  Discharged from service, <date type="servicedischarge" when="1865-06-20">June 20th, 1865</date>,
                    on account of deafness of the left ear and facial neuralgia, by <name
                        type="person" key="245">Assistant Surgeon H. Allen</name>, <name
                        type="organization" key="190">U. S. A.</name>  His name does not appear on the Pension List. </p>            
